## ğŸª Milgrain: Vintage Romance

Milgrain comes from the French word *mille-grain*, meaning â€œa thousand grains.â€ It refers to a decorative technique where tiny metal beads are carefully applied along the edges of the ring using a beading tool.

Popularized in the **Edwardian** and **Art Deco** periods, milgrain carries an air of vintage refinement. It was originally used to soften the sparkle of diamonds and mimic the lace detailing of garments in that era.

Milgrain rings are cherished by those with nostalgic heartsâ€”those who believe romance lives in the details.

